Scuse me darling.

509
00:28:11.272 --> 00:28:12.752
Oh no, you haven't got your belt.

510
00:28:12.752 --> 00:28:17.411
His kind of a belt, it's woven.

511
00:28:17.411 --> 00:28:20.811
It has a lot of the patterns that we saw today.

512
00:28:20.811 --> 00:28:22.351
So for our people,

513
00:28:22.351 --> 00:28:23.611
<v Regina>It's always been there.</v>

514
00:28:23.611 --> 00:28:25.871
<v ->we were being a literate people,</v>

515
00:28:25.871 --> 00:28:28.511
we were told we were illiterate,

516
00:28:28.511 --> 00:28:29.791
and I've had to say to people,

517
00:28:29.791 --> 00:28:33.011
do you know what literate really means?

518
00:28:33.011 --> 00:28:35.931
Can you read nature?

519
00:28:35.931 --> 00:28:39.931
Can you read what we say to you in the house?

520
00:28:39.931 --> 00:28:42.911
No you can't.

521
00:28:42.911 --> 00:28:45.971
We can work yours out just like this,

522
00:28:45.971 --> 00:28:49.331
just knowing the patterns.

523
00:28:51.881 --> 00:28:54.731
For me, I learned about the western world,

524
00:28:54.731 --> 00:28:57.011
it was no problem.

525
00:28:57.011 --> 00:29:01.131
I could do things just through my mind,

526
00:29:01.131 --> 00:29:03.871
and run circles around the teachers

527
00:29:03.871 --> 00:29:07.471
because the teachers were all white, most of them,

528
00:29:07.471 --> 00:29:10.711
left brained, for God's sake.

529
00:29:10.711 --> 00:29:13.731
We're whole brained for learning people.

530
00:29:13.731 --> 00:29:14.971
We work with the whole brain.

531
00:29:14.971 --> 00:29:16.309
We always have.

532
00:29:16.309 --> 00:29:19.949
All our posture dances help us with whole brain learning.

533
00:29:19.949 --> 00:29:24.109
So that we can move into the super consciousness.

534
00:29:24.109 --> 00:29:28.409
So our teachers, if we wanted to please them,

535
00:29:28.409 --> 00:29:31.169
we would move in on the left brain.

536
00:29:31.169 --> 00:29:35.729
If we wanted to really get them raving mad,

537
00:29:35.729 --> 00:29:37.847
we would move in on the right.

538
00:29:37.847 --> 00:29:40.107
They couldn't handle it.

539
00:29:40.107 --> 00:29:42.307
<v Regina>How did that express itself with them?</v>

540
00:29:42.307 --> 00:29:44.507
<v ->Well what does it tell the western world?</v>

541
00:29:44.507 --> 00:29:46.547
Get into gear.

542
00:29:46.547 --> 00:29:49.647
Whole brain learning is a part of us.

543
00:29:49.647 --> 00:29:51.177
<v Regina>Absolutely.</v>

544
00:29:52.357 --> 00:29:56.087
What is happening with the Maori today?

545
00:29:56.087 --> 00:29:57.767
Who succeeds you?

546
00:29:57.767 --> 00:30:00.807
You're from a long line of people who know and see.

547
00:30:00.807 --> 00:30:03.367
<v ->Oh no, that won't be a problem, you know.</v>

548
00:30:03.367 --> 00:30:04.507
<v Regina>The traditions or...</v>

549
00:30:04.507 --> 00:30:07.627
<v ->No, it won't be a problem, it goes down in a way.</v>

550
00:30:07.627 --> 00:30:09.367
It's in the genes.

551
00:30:09.367 --> 00:30:10.507
<v Regina>So it really doesn't matter if</v>

552
00:30:10.507 --> 00:30:13.107
the outside look changes?

553
00:30:13.107 --> 00:30:14.907
It's still a part of you?

554
00:30:14.907 --> 00:30:16.747
<v ->It's still, I mean no one in it,</v>

555
00:30:16.747 --> 00:30:18.787
most people in our country,

556
00:30:18.787 --> 00:30:20.667
when I was in the department of education,

557
00:30:20.667 --> 00:30:22.787
I had a very senior position.

558
00:30:22.787 --> 00:30:26.227
None of them knew that I was a "tahuna",

559
00:30:26.227 --> 00:30:31.027
wasn't their business, right?

560
00:30:31.027 --> 00:30:35.087
But I knew their world and I knew it inside out.

561
00:30:35.087 --> 00:30:37.567
And I'm one of the few people in New Zealand

562
00:30:37.567 --> 00:30:39.807
who has represented our country

563
00:30:39.807 --> 00:30:44.807
at conferences for teachers of English, internationally.

564
00:30:45.287 --> 00:30:47.967
I've had my white brothers and sisters say,

565
00:30:47.967 --> 00:30:50.027
for God's sake Rose, how come you're going?

566
00:30:50.027 --> 00:30:51.747
And I said obviously my English is

567
00:30:51.747 --> 00:30:54.287
completely superior to yours.

568
00:30:54.287 --> 00:30:55.707
(laughter)

569
00:30:55.707 --> 00:30:57.567
And it is my second language.

570
00:30:57.567 --> 00:31:01.287
<v Regina>Rose, you've been bestowed a lot of honors.</v>

571
00:31:01.287 --> 00:31:02.447
<v ->I have.</v>

572
00:31:02.447 --> 00:31:03.907
I deserve them.

573
00:31:03.907 --> 00:31:07.207
I deserve them for sure because it's been a hard job.

574
00:31:07.207 --> 00:31:10.727
It has been a hard job working with left-brained people.

575
00:31:10.727 --> 00:31:12.147
It really has.

576
00:31:12.147 --> 00:31:13.847
Hard job.

577
00:31:13.847 --> 00:31:18.407
I started in 1956, a group of us Maori people,

578
00:31:18.407 --> 00:31:20.987
working with the system of New Zealand

579
00:31:20.987 --> 00:31:23.147
in terms of education.

580
00:31:23.147 --> 00:31:27.467
We finally got through by the year 1974,

581
00:31:27.467 --> 00:31:30.047
and then Maori became accepted

582
00:31:30.047 --> 00:31:33.467
as part and parcel of New Zealand.

583
00:31:33.467 --> 00:31:35.167
<v Regina>If you can talk to mothers now</v>

584
00:31:35.167 --> 00:31:38.807
in the western world, you've seen how we raise our children.

585
00:31:38.807 --> 00:31:41.267
You've seen what the education system is like.

586
00:31:41.267 --> 00:31:43.187
You have a mother watching right now

587
00:31:43.187 --> 00:31:46.067
with a little child, an infant.

588
00:31:46.067 --> 00:31:50.427
What information can you pass on to them?

589
00:31:50.427 --> 00:31:54.067
<v ->The child is a learner and a teacher.</v>

590
00:31:54.067 --> 00:31:56.287
The child comes in with insight,

591
00:31:56.287 --> 00:31:58.667
everything from the other side.

592
00:31:58.667 --> 00:32:01.685
By the time they're eight in the western world,

593
00:32:01.685 --> 00:32:03.845
that's repressed in them.

594
00:32:03.845 --> 00:32:06.045
You get parents that say to children,

595
00:32:06.045 --> 00:32:08.505
yes I used to be like that darling.

596
00:32:08.505 --> 00:32:11.305
I used to have little friends too.

597
00:32:11.305 --> 00:32:15.605
The child knows about the little friends and can see them.

598
00:32:17.495 --> 00:32:20.965
And so they're ridiculing to a certain extent.

599
00:32:20.965 --> 00:32:23.465
Something that is a natural, vital part.

600
00:32:23.465 --> 00:32:24.845
<v Regina>Patronizing them, yes.</v>

601
00:32:24.845 --> 00:32:29.245
<v ->And in New Zealand, we let our children go</v>

602
00:32:29.245 --> 00:32:32.205
because they learn from firsthand experience.

603
00:32:32.205 --> 00:32:35.545
We also treat them as our equals.

604
00:32:35.545 --> 00:32:38.025
We do not speak down.

605
00:32:38.025 --> 00:32:40.905
The other thing is that we learn from them.

606
00:32:40.905 --> 00:32:44.305
For example, I taught my grandparents' generation

607
00:32:44.305 --> 00:32:45.825
how to rock and roll.

608
00:32:45.825 --> 00:32:47.445
(laughter)

609
00:32:47.445 --> 00:32:51.465
And they taught me the Charleston.

610
00:32:51.465 --> 00:32:56.165
So I mean, in my culture, the generations learn

611
00:32:56.165 --> 00:33:01.165
from each other and we have intergenerational teaching.

612
00:33:01.425 --> 00:33:04.685
At home, our grandchildren live with us,

613
00:33:04.685 --> 00:33:08.925
and our children, and we also have great grandchildren.

614
00:33:08.925 --> 00:33:11.745
So that what we're transmitting,

615
00:33:11.745 --> 00:33:13.525
we are the first teachers.

616
00:33:13.525 --> 00:33:17.225
The grandparents are the first teachers in my culture

617
00:33:17.225 --> 00:33:20.945
because the parents are busy making a living,

618
00:33:20.945 --> 00:33:24.145
building up the economic base.

619
00:33:24.145 --> 00:33:27.645
And we have all the patience in the world

620
00:33:27.645 --> 00:33:29.965
with our grandchildren.

621
00:33:29.965 --> 00:33:31.345
<v Regina>It seems so important because</v>

622
00:33:31.345 --> 00:33:35.385
here, the family has been so fragmented,

623
00:33:35.385 --> 00:33:40.145
and it seems through sheer economic impetus alone,

624
00:33:40.145 --> 00:33:41.625
it's going to be necessary for people

625
00:33:41.625 --> 00:33:43.445
to begin coming back together again,

626
00:33:43.445 --> 00:33:46.365
which I think is fabulous.

627
00:33:46.365 --> 00:33:48.365
Why do we think we should toss our children out

628
00:33:48.365 --> 00:33:52.205
at the age of 18 and we have our own little house,

629
00:33:52.205 --> 00:33:53.885
each person has their own little house,

630
00:33:53.885 --> 00:33:56.425
or individuals, their own little condiminium

631
00:33:56.425 --> 00:33:57.865
separate from each other.

632
00:33:57.865 --> 00:33:59.605
It doesn't make sense that we live like this.

633
00:33:59.605 --> 00:34:01.925
<v ->That is a constant battle for us in New Zealand,</v>

634
00:34:01.925 --> 00:34:03.885
the Maori, because we're used to

635
00:34:03.885 --> 00:34:08.825
family oriented situations and living,

636
00:34:08.825 --> 00:34:13.185
and they are forever trying to separate the genders,

637
00:34:13.185 --> 00:34:17.205
forever trying to separate the generations,

638
00:34:17.205 --> 00:34:22.085
by trying to come across our entire way of thinking.

639
00:34:22.085 --> 00:34:25.065
And I've said to our people, no, we can not afford

640
00:34:25.065 --> 00:34:30.005
to follow in their footsteps because for us,

641
00:34:30.005 --> 00:34:35.005
we have to remember that we link in to the cosmos,

642
00:34:37.482 --> 00:34:41.301
that we link into, that there's no limit to our thinking,

643
00:34:41.301 --> 00:34:43.941
and our children, they are treasures.

644
00:34:43.941 --> 00:34:45.619
They are miracles.

645
00:34:45.619 --> 00:34:49.619
"Hatinotanga", absolute treasures.

646
00:34:49.619 --> 00:34:53.539
And so they have the right to be true to themselves.

647
00:34:53.539 --> 00:34:56.709
They are not possessions.

648
00:34:58.879 --> 00:35:03.879
They are divine beings that have a right

649
00:35:04.605 --> 00:35:06.875
to be true to themselves.

650
00:35:06.875 --> 00:35:09.441
(thunder)

651
00:35:09.441 --> 00:35:10.861
<v Regina>Confirmation.</v>

652
00:35:10.861 --> 00:35:11.721
<v ->You see that?</v>

653
00:35:11.721 --> 00:35:12.821
<v Regina>The first thunder.</v>

654
00:35:12.821 --> 00:35:13.561
<v ->You see that?</v>

655
00:35:13.561 --> 00:35:16.321
<v Regina>Yes, that is perfect.</v>

656
00:35:16.321 --> 00:35:17.201
<v ->You see that.</v>

657
00:35:17.201 --> 00:35:18.881
<v Regina>And every one of us has that right.</v>

658
00:35:18.881 --> 00:35:22.001
<v ->You see that we have that right.</v>

659
00:35:22.001 --> 00:35:24.821
My grandson, he's 27 and one of them,

660
00:35:24.821 --> 00:35:28.181
he's driving me crazy, but it's not my journey,

661
00:35:28.181 --> 00:35:29.721
it is his.

662
00:35:29.721 --> 00:35:31.981
And I have to respect that.

663
00:35:31.981 --> 00:35:34.621
You see, I'm one of those people that has spoken out

664
00:35:34.621 --> 00:35:39.621
against genetic engineering, against in vitro fertilization,

665
00:35:39.641 --> 00:35:43.481
and I remember someone saying that you know,

666
00:35:43.481 --> 00:35:45.921
the sexual act can be so clumsy,

667
00:35:45.921 --> 00:35:48.441
and I said oh is that right?

668
00:35:48.441 --> 00:35:51.141
So you would prefer to have a woman

669
00:35:51.141 --> 00:35:54.721
drinking wine in one room at the hospital

670
00:35:54.721 --> 00:35:59.181
surrounded by parts that look like penises?

671
00:35:59.181 --> 00:36:01.781
And then you have a man in another room

672
00:36:01.781 --> 00:36:06.781
reading a Penthouse magazine and you dare say to me

673
00:36:07.621 --> 00:36:12.401
that a natural relationship is clumsy?

674
00:36:12.401 --> 00:36:15.701
(laughter)

675
00:36:15.701 --> 00:36:20.241
And do you have Maori donor fathers?

676
00:36:20.241 --> 00:36:24.061
Oh no, they didn't in New Zealand.

677
00:36:24.061 --> 00:36:26.201
I said do you have Jewish donor fathers?

678
00:36:26.201 --> 00:36:27.621
Nope.

679
00:36:27.621 --> 00:36:29.961
I said that's very interesting.

680
00:36:29.961 --> 00:36:33.481
So all of the donor fathers are Caucasian, are they?

681
00:36:33.481 --> 00:36:38.421
Said, oh yes, well we have the IQ and all this and all that,

682
00:36:38.421 --> 00:36:40.261
and I said oh is that right.

683
00:36:40.261 --> 00:36:42.521
So if two people meet in the future,

684
00:36:42.521 --> 00:36:47.341
they say I hope your donor father's not number 17

685
00:36:47.341 --> 00:36:49.161
because that's mine, you know?

686
00:36:49.161 --> 00:36:51.201
(laughter)

687
00:36:51.201 --> 00:36:56.201
For me, a Maori, that believes in the sacredness

688
00:36:58.201 --> 00:37:02.601
of the union of the mother and father energies,

689
00:37:02.601 --> 00:37:05.401
and we are linked into that.

690
00:37:05.401 --> 00:37:09.801
Joe and I, he is my right, I am his left.

691
00:37:09.801 --> 00:37:13.341
That's just beyond...

692
00:37:13.341 --> 00:37:17.721
And for me, in the Maori culture,

693
00:37:17.721 --> 00:37:19.881
genealogy is important, not saying

694
00:37:19.881 --> 00:37:22.741
number 17 is my donor father.

695
00:37:22.741 --> 00:37:27.741
It is meant to say my mother is so-and-so,

696
00:37:30.161 --> 00:37:32.561
that my father is so-and-so, then being able

697
00:37:32.561 --> 00:37:35.583
to go back in with the generations.

698
00:37:35.583 --> 00:37:38.763
Very important, our genealogy is important.

699
00:37:38.763 --> 00:37:40.983
That's why I can sit here.

700
00:37:40.983 --> 00:37:45.083
I can stand up with confidence because I know who I am.

701
00:37:45.083 --> 00:37:49.883
I know from whence I came and I know where I'm going.

702
00:37:49.883 --> 00:37:52.183
How many people know that?

703
00:37:52.183 --> 00:37:54.143
<v Regina>Not many.</v>

704
00:37:54.143 --> 00:37:56.163
Not many in the west.

705
00:37:56.163 --> 00:38:00.163
<v ->It is not enough to say go under father number 17,</v>

706
00:38:00.163 --> 00:38:05.163
IQ 160, no.

707
00:38:05.563 --> 00:38:07.643
In fact you had a situation here in the States

708
00:38:07.643 --> 00:38:10.823
where the donor father was ugly ass,

709
00:38:10.823 --> 00:38:13.543
and a lot of the children ended up looking like that.

710
00:38:13.543 --> 00:38:16.203
Well, right.

711
00:38:16.203 --> 00:38:17.983
<v Regina>Well again, it's trying to put value</v>

712
00:38:17.983 --> 00:38:20.983
on all the externals instead of the whole.

713
00:38:20.983 --> 00:38:23.063
<v ->And what I've found out, a lot of people,</v>

714
00:38:23.063 --> 00:38:24.943
the reason why they have that old,

715
00:38:24.943 --> 00:38:26.303
they have to have a child is because

716
00:38:26.303 --> 00:38:29.363
they see them as a possession.

717
00:38:29.363 --> 00:38:30.163
Possession.

718
00:38:30.163 --> 00:38:31.083
<v Regina>Just like a nice car.</v>

719
00:38:31.083 --> 00:38:34.063
Something else to round out the picture of life.

720
00:38:34.063 --> 00:38:36.943
<v ->You see, we had lesbians who attended the conference</v>

721
00:38:36.943 --> 00:38:41.204
where I spoke out against in vitro fertilization.

722
00:38:41.204 --> 00:38:45.343
And they said to me, these were Maori lesbians, okay?

723
00:38:45.343 --> 00:38:48.103
They said well we really want children.

724
00:38:48.103 --> 00:38:51.463
I said get on to your tribal brothers.

725
00:38:51.463 --> 00:38:56.043
At least you will know their genealogy.

726
00:38:56.043 --> 00:38:57.763
And it's happened.

727
00:38:57.763 --> 00:38:59.243
I said don't go there.

728
00:38:59.243 --> 00:39:01.943
Don't even consider it.

729
00:39:01.943 --> 00:39:04.843
It is alien.

730
00:39:04.843 --> 00:39:09.843
For example, Jesus, I saw him smash these tubes.

731
00:39:09.843 --> 00:39:12.103
I said to him, the only time I ever read

732
00:39:12.103 --> 00:39:16.543
about you losing your temper was in the temple.

733
00:39:16.543 --> 00:39:21.543
It was his anger against in vitro fertilization.

734
00:39:23.103 --> 00:39:26.203
Now people might say good God, who is this woman?

735
00:39:26.203 --> 00:39:28.703
Too bad people.

736
00:39:28.703 --> 00:39:31.623
I've seen Jesus and I know him.

737
00:39:31.623 --> 00:39:34.523
The other thing is, he loves me for myself.

738
00:39:34.523 --> 00:39:37.983
He has never told me to be any different.

739
00:39:37.983 --> 00:39:39.203
Never.

740
00:39:39.203 --> 00:39:44.144
All I know from him is love, unconditional love.

741
00:39:44.144 --> 00:39:48.423
Not telling me to change or to be any different.

742
00:39:48.423 --> 00:39:51.703
And so for me, when I have so-called Christians

743
00:39:51.703 --> 00:39:53.123
who talk to me, I say to them,

744
00:39:53.123 --> 00:39:55.863
do you really know what you're talking about?

745
00:39:55.863 --> 00:39:59.944
Are you really practicing unconditional love?

746
00:39:59.944 --> 00:40:04.944
Are you really promoting what Jesus was all about?

747
00:40:06.103 --> 00:40:08.443
A challenge.

748
00:40:08.443 --> 00:40:10.183
<v Regina>It is a challenge, and on the subject</v>

749
00:40:10.183 --> 00:40:13.483
of this about the judgement that we have of each other,

750
00:40:13.483 --> 00:40:15.883
and putting on ourselves as well,

751
00:40:15.883 --> 00:40:18.003
as I asked a moment ago for you to please speak

752
00:40:18.003 --> 00:40:20.643
to a mother regarding a child,

753
00:40:20.643 --> 00:40:22.683
what about the mother herself?

754
00:40:22.683 --> 00:40:25.883
In the western world, in America in particular,

755
00:40:25.883 --> 00:40:29.023
the women are so full of self-loathing

756
00:40:29.023 --> 00:40:32.543
because maybe they age,

757
00:40:32.543 --> 00:40:35.583
maybe they gain 10 or 20 or 30 pounds.

758
00:40:35.583 --> 00:40:37.503
<v ->Oh look, we love ourselves, you see.</v>

759
00:40:37.503 --> 00:40:38.963
That's how we are.

760
00:40:38.963 --> 00:40:40.463
We just love ourselves.

761
00:40:40.463 --> 00:40:42.443
I said Joe's a lucky man because

762
00:40:42.443 --> 00:40:44.263
he's got interests over the years with

763
00:40:44.263 --> 00:40:45.743
me putting on weight, you know.

764
00:40:45.743 --> 00:40:46.443
(laughter)

